# Mobile App User Guide 📱

## Overview
The **Daily Habit Tracker** has been converted into a mobile application using Capacitor. You can now run it as a native app on Android and iOS devices.

## Requirements
- **Android**: Android Studio installed.
- **iOS**: Xcode installed (Mac only).

## How to Run

### Android (Galaxy, Pixel, etc.)
1.  **Open Project**: Run the following command in your terminal:
    ```bash
    npm run mobile:open:android
    ```
    This will launch **Android Studio**.

2.  **Wait for Sync**:
    - When Android Studio opens for the first time, it needs to download some files (Gradle sync). Look at the bottom right corner; wait until the loading bars finish.

3.  **Connect Device**:
    - Connect your Android phone to your PC via USB.
    - Make sure **USB Debugging** is enabled on your phone (in Developer Options).
    - You should see your phone's name in the top toolbar of Android Studio.

4.  **Run App**:
    - Click the **Green Play Button (▶)** in the top toolbar.
    - The app will build and install on your phone!

### iOS (iPhone, iPad) - *Mac Only*
1.  **Open Project**: Run the following command:
    ```bash
    npm run mobile:open:ios
    ```
    This will launch **Xcode**.

2.  **Select Team**:
    - Click on the "App" project in the left navigator.
    - Go to **Signing & Capabilities**.
    - Select your Apple ID in the **Team** dropdown.

3.  **Run App**:
    - Connect your iPhone to your Mac.
    - Select your phone from the device list at the top.
    - Click the **Play Button (▶)**.

## Troubleshooting
- **"Unable to launch Android Studio"**: Make sure Android Studio is installed properly. You can also open it manually and select the `android` folder in the project directory.
- **Build Errors**: Try running `npx cap sync` in the terminal to ensure the latest code is synchronized.
